<h2>Why v1 failed and v2 worked — what I changed</h2>

<div class="flex">
<div class="col box warn">
<h3>v1: dead-end pattern</h3>
<ul>
<li>I trusted the public docs (<code>docs.omnara.com</code>): they describe an "agent SDK" model with <code>POST /api/v1/messages/agent</code> on host <code>agent.omnara.com</code>.</li>
<li>That host doesn't even <strong>resolve</strong> any more (<code>Could not resolve host: agent.omnara.com</code> via DNS-over-HTTPS too).</li>
<li>I tried every variation on <code>api.omnara.com</code>: <code>/api/v1/agent-instances</code>, <code>/messages/agent</code>, <code>/messages/pending</code> — all 404.</li>
<li>The frontend bundle on <code>www.omnara.com</code> only ships marketing routes (<code>/auth/sync-user</code>, <code>/auth/validate-email</code>) — dashboard routes are lazy-loaded behind login I can't trigger.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="col box ok">
<h3>v2: what unstuck it</h3>
<ul>
<li>Realized the omnara CLI binary at <code>~/.omnara/bin/omnara</code> (108 MB Bun-compiled blob) <em>is</em> the production client and bakes every endpoint string into the binary.</li>
<li>Ran <code>strings ~/.omnara/bin/omnara | grep -oE "/api/v[0-9]/[a-zA-Z0-9_/-]+"</code> → got 25 unique paths including <code>/api/v1/user-sessions</code>, <code>/api/v1/workspaces/{wid}/sessions</code>, <code>/api/v1/machines</code>, <code>/api/v1/worktrees/...</code>.</li>
<li><strong>None of these are documented anywhere on docs.omnara.com.</strong> They are the "agent dashboard" backend resources, not the legacy agent-SDK endpoints.</li>
<li>For send-message specifically, I went one level deeper: searched the binary for <code>agent-sessions</code> in templated path strings (<code>${...}</code>) and found <code>/api/v1/user-sessions/${y}/agent-sessions/${f}/messages</code> inside a <code>fetchSessionMessages()</code> function that paginates by <code>before_id</code>.</li>
<li>Then probed the POST: 422 told me the field name (<code>text</code>) → 200 on <code>{"text":"..."}</code>.</li>
<li><strong>One-liner that explains it all:</strong> the public docs describe the v0 product (single-agent SDK that calls in); the live product is v2 (dashboard that calls out via daemon + relay), and only the binary tells you the new shape.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<h2>How Omnara's API actually works (≠ the public docs)</h2>

<div class="diagram">                                    Cloudflare
                                        |
   you (web/iOS/CLI) ----HTTPS---->  api.omnara.com  <----WSS----  ~/.omnara daemon
                                  |                 |              (on each machine)
                                  | PAT / Supabase  |                       |
                                  | JWT             | relays                | spawns
                                  v                 v                       v
                         FastAPI (REST)      relay_server          claude_code / codex
                         . workspaces        (wss://api.../        subprocess in
                         . user-sessions      ws/machines)         workspace dir
                         . worktrees                                       |
                         . machines                                        v
                         . messages (read & write!)            ~/.claude/projects/...jsonl
</div>

