<h2>Tracker design — "one Omnara to rule them all"</h2>

<div class="flex">
<div class="col box">
<h3>Architecture</h3>
<pre style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.4;">+----------------------+     poll 15s      +-----------------+
| api.omnara.com REST  | <---------------- |    Tracker       |
| - user-sessions      |  push messages    |  poller + db    |
| - messages (R/W)     | ----------------> |  todo extractor |
| - workspaces         |                   |  dispatch CLI   |
| - machines           |                   |  web UI         |
+----------------------+                   +-----------------+
        ^                                          |
        | wss                                      | DM / page
        |                                          v
+----------------------+                   +-----------------+
| ~/.omnara daemons    |                   | Slack / phone   |
| on every machine     |                   | (only when      |
| (claude / codex)     |                   |  AWAITING_INPUT)|
+----------------------+                   +-----------------+</pre>
</div>

<div class="col box">
<h3>Core loop</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Poll</strong> <code>GET /user-sessions</code> every 15 s, diff <code>last_message_at</code>+<code>work_status</code> per agent_session_id</li>
<li><strong>Index content</strong> on diff: <code>GET .../messages?limit=20&before_id=&lt;last_seen&gt;</code> → store new msgs in sqlite</li>
<li><strong>Extract TODOs</strong> with a small LLM (Haiku/Flash) reading just the new messages</li>
<li><strong>Dispatch</strong>: <code>POST /workspaces/{wid}/sessions</code> with templated prompts, choose machine via <code>GET /machines</code> (online filter)</li>
<li><strong>Auto-respond</strong>: when <code>work_status=AWAITING_INPUT</code> for &gt;N min, either (a) inject a templated reply via <code>POST .../messages</code> (b) Slack-DM Steve with the dashboard URL</li>
<li><strong>Garbage-collect</strong>: <code>DELETE</code> sessions older than X with no recent activity</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="box info">
<h3>Why this scales</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Single PAT, all machines.</strong> Same user_id across every Omnara-connected daemon. No SSH bouncing required to tracker.</li>
<li><strong>REST only.</strong> No WebSocket protocol needed — POST messages goes through the relay automatically. Tracker can be stateless (any region).</li>
<li><strong>Idempotent.</strong> <code>workspaces/ensure</code>, <code>worktrees/ensure</code>, send-message with <code>client_message_id</code> → safe retry.</li>
<li><strong>Deep-linkable.</strong> <code>https://www.omnara.com/dashboard/sessions/{usid}</code> for human takeover from any tracker UI.</li>
<li><strong>No daemon code.</strong> Fully out-of-band — daemon never needs to know tracker exists.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="box warn">
<h3>Watch out</h3>
<ul>
<li>PAT is a long-lived JWT (no <code>exp</code> on personal access tokens). If <code>~/.omnara/creds.json</code> leaks, attacker gets shell-equivalent access on every machine in <code>GET /machines</code>. Rotate via dashboard UI.</li>
<li>These endpoints are <strong>not public</strong>. Wrap in a thin client and pin to <code>daemon_version</code> seen in the response → assert + alert on schema drift.</li>
<li>Server has no client-source check on <code>POST messages</code>. Defense lives in the <em>agent</em>, not the API. Live session 322780f9 just demonstrated good agent-side rejection — but <em>nothing prevents</em> a hostile tool from injecting tasks. Treat agents as untrusted recipients of user-turn content.</li>
<li>Auto-dispatch in trusted dirs only, or use <code>start_sandbox:true</code>.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Curl recipes (paste-ready)</h2>

<pre>PAT=$(jq -r .pat ~/.omnara/creds.json)
B=https://api.omnara.com
H="-H Authorization:Bearer $PAT"

# 1. list everything
curl -sH "Authorization: Bearer $PAT" "$B/api/v1/user-sessions" | jq '.sessions | length'

# 2. read message history of a session
USID=...
ASID=...
curl -sH "Authorization: Bearer $PAT" \
  "$B/api/v1/user-sessions/$USID/agent-sessions/$ASID/messages?limit=20" | jq '.messages[].payload.content.text // empty'

# 3. SEND a message into an existing session
curl -sH "Authorization: Bearer $PAT" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -X POST "$B/api/v1/user-sessions/$USID/agent-sessions/$ASID/messages" \
  -d '{"text":"keep going, focus on tests"}'

# 4. dispatch a new job
WID=3d658c9c-9f65-486b-86ca-3b8fd59665b0   # personal workspace
curl -sH "Authorization: Bearer $PAT" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -X POST "$B/api/v1/workspaces/$WID/sessions" \
  -d '{"directory":"/sensei-fs-3/users/zouyang/personal","initial_message":"hello from tracker"}'

# 5. ensure a brand-new workspace
MID=7b70e683-cd04-4827-9879-7bf8fb305838   # this pod
curl -sH "Authorization: Bearer $PAT" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -X POST "$B/api/v1/workspaces/ensure" \
